    "raptors": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Raptors",
      "league": "NBA",
      "record": "46-36",
      "detail": "3rd in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors' playoff firestorm ignited in Cleveland last night, where Scottie Barnes shrugged off the road noise with a defiant \"That shit don't matter\" after practice, channeling the grit that's carried this 46-36 squad &mdash; third in the Atlantic, no. 5 seed &mdash; through a grueling regular season on a one-game win streak. <strong>The series sits deadlocked at 1-1 against the fourth-seeded Cavaliers</strong>, Toronto snatching momentum with a gritty Game 2 steal on enemy ice, their defense clamping down just enough to expose Cleveland's shaky fifth starter while Barnes erupted for 28 points and 10 boards, the All-Star forward proving he's the heartbeat in this do-or-die dance. What went right? Barnes' swagger &mdash; the kid's averaging a playoff double-double already &mdash; and a bench that finally barked back. Wrong? Perimeter lapses that let the Cavs breathe too easy in Game 1. This is the crescendo, the 5.0 games-back regular-season grind boiling over into blood-and-guts basketball. <strong>Game 3 thunders Thursday at 12:30 Eastern back home in Scotiabank Arena</strong> &mdash; win it, and the Raptors seize series control; fold, and Cleveland smells blood. The North wakes up hungry today.",
        "updated": "Updated April 16, 2026"
      },
