      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft smoke thickens around Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left them third in the NFC East, nine games back, and clutching the No. 7 pick like a lifeline to redemption. <strong>Ohio State safety Caleb Downs toured Ashburn this week</strong>, fueling buzz that he's the Commanders' floor at seven &mdash; his Matt Patricia scheme fit screams instant-impact, with insiders whispering he could slide no lower. GM Adam Peters plays it coy, eyeing positional value but open to linebacker Sonny Styles, RB Jeremiyah Love, or even Downs over premium spots, while odds-makers oddly peg Love as the favorite despite glaring holes at receiver opposite Terry McLaurin &mdash; Carnell Tate and Makai Lemon visited too &mdash; plus secondary and center after a quiet free agency. Trading down tempts, especially with just six picks after shipping seconds and fourths for Laremy Tunsil last spring; Day 2 chatter even floats dealing Daron Payne for ammo. Peters hosted top-30 prospects at Top Golf Tuesday, the final pre-draft frenzy before Pittsburgh. <strong>One week out, watch if Quinn pushes edge like David Bailey in mocks or swaps picks &mdash; this board will define 2026's ascent.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 16, 2026"
      },
